OL,3,CResidents finally given accommodation
OL,4,Cweek on from flood evacuation
OL,6,FMore than 400 people had to be
OL,7,Fevacuated from the converted mill on
OL,8,FNew Year's Day after the building's
OL,9,Fcar park and lower floors were
OL,10,Fflooded, cutting off water and power
OL,11,Fsupplies and leaving residents
OL,12,Fstranded.
OL,14,FIn their letter, council leader,
OL,15,FCouncillor Mark Hunter, and Chief
OL,16,FExecutive, Michael Cullen, said the
OL,17,Fdelay in restoring utilities was
OL,18,F"unacceptable", urging owners Arwal
OL,19,FInvestments and management firm CERT
OL,20,Fto help residents, "many of whom are
OL,21,Fnow in complete crisis".
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/8
