OL,3,CResidents finally given accommodation
OL,4,Cweek on from flood evacuation
OL,6,FThe councillors claim people living in
OL,7,Fthe apartments are struggling without
OL,8,Fclear guidance on insurance claims or
OL,9,Ftemporary accommodation, with some
OL,10,Fforced to pay for hotel accommodation
OL,11,F"up front".
OL,13,FHowever, they added that "desperation
OL,14,Fis growing" with many residents now
OL,15,Freporting that financially they have
OL,16,Fto move back in to the building
OL,17,Fwithout electricity, water or
OL,18,Fappropriate safety measures in place
OL,19,Fto protect them.
